The chemical composition of the synthesized thin films is compared with the atomic stoichiometry of Cu (25%), Zn (12.5%), Sn (12.5%), and S (50%) and is tabulated in Table 3. Figure 6 depicts the composition of the CZTS thin films for various samples. As it is seen from the table, out of all the samples, the S1-T30 sample shows a good composition compared to other samples. From the elemental composition, it is evident that the Cu2S is predominant in the S1-T60 sample which is in line with the XRD analysis. In the case of the S2 series, copper was increased and zinc was decreased with increased sulfurization time during which tin and sulfur remained the same without much variation leading to the formation of the SnS secondary phase. Figure 7 shows the EDS spectrum of the S1-T30 sample.Table 3
